Crimson Text Regular (CrimsonText-Regular.ttf)

name

NID 0 (1, 0, 0, 0)

'Copyright' has invalid entry.

Name table entry contains line break, but shouldn't:
'Copyright (c) 2010, Sebastian Kosch (sebastian@aldusleaf.org),[
]with Reserved Font Name "Crimson Text".[
]This Font Software is licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1.[
]This license is available with a FAQ at: http://scripts.sil.org/OFL'

Error

Crimson Text Regular (CrimsonText-Regular.ttf)

name

Mac NID 0 (1, 0, 0, 0)

Mac NID 0, Copyright.

Please verify agains spec.
Mac NID 0 is 'Copyright (c) 2010, Sebastian Kosch (sebastian@aldusleaf.org),
with Reserved Font Name "Crimson Text".
This Font Software is licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1.
This license is available with a FAQ at: http://scripts.sil.org/OFL'

Crimson Text Italic (CrimsonText-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CrimsonText-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Crimson Text SemiBold Regular (CrimsonText-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Crimson Text' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Crimson Text SemiBold'.

Crimson Text SemiBold Italic (CrimsonText-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CrimsonText-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Crimson Text SemiBold Italic (CrimsonText-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Crimson Text' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Crimson Text SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'CrimsonText-Bold', Everything looks good.

NID 6 is 'CrimsonText-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

GPOS

-/-

Simple check if kern feature in GPOS table.

Font does not have GPOS table/kerning. Please investigate if this meets requirements.

Warning

Crimson Text Regular (CrimsonText-Regular.ttf)

kern

-/-

Check if 'kern' table in TTF font.

Font has 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.
For example: PowerPoint only supports a flat GPOS kerning or a kern table. So, if the customer requires PowerPoint support, a kern table is necessary.
